  "time_ut": 1659458140,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "New notification regarding fuel permit",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lanka Information and Communication Technology Service has requested the public to register a new fuel permit as soon as possible.",
        "Do not abuse the new method of obtaining fuel. So far 51 lakh vehicles have been registered, Dasun Hegoda, director of the Sri Lankan Information and Communication Technology Service, said.",
        "He further informed that only 6 lakh vehicles have been registered under the QR system on 1st August and this new system has been implemented in 726 petrol stations owned by Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation and 132 petrol stations owned by IOC.",
        "He said that under this system it will be possible to identify those who are trying to obtain fuel illegally and take legal action against them."
      ],
